滚石乐队分享 Lady Gaga 和 Stevie Wonder 的新单曲“Sweet Sounds Of Heaven” https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-share-lady-gaga-and-stevie-wonder-featuring-new-single-sweet-sounds-of-heaven-3506066?utm_source= rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=滚石乐队分享 Lady-Gaga 和 stevie-wonder-featureing-new-single-sweet-sounds-of-heavenAnagricel Duran Thu, 28 Sep 2023 16:59:40 +0000 Music NewsNewsRockhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3506066 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="滚石乐队。图片来源：马克·塞利格" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这首歌是乐队即将发行的唱片“Hackney Diamonds”中发行的第二首单曲</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-share-lady-gaga-and-stevie-wonder-featuring-new-single-sweet-sounds-of-heaven-3506066">滚石乐队分享 Lady Gaga 和 Stevie Wonder 的新单曲“Sweet Sounds Of Heaven”的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="滚石乐队。图片来源：马克·塞利格" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones.-Credit-Mark-Seliger-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="/artists/the-rolling-stones">滚石乐队</a>分享了由<a href="/artists/lady-gaga">Lady Gaga</a>和<a href="/artists/stevie-wonder">Stevie Wonder</a>主演的最新单曲“Sweet Sounds Of Heaven”。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-rolling-stones-new-album-release-date-hackney-diamonds-3494545">滚石乐队的回归带来了更大的冲击</a></strong></li></ul><p>这首充满福音气息的歌曲让人想起乐队的一些经典热门歌曲，如“You Can&#39;t Always Get What You Want”和“Shine A Light”，Wonder 接管了 Fender Rhodes、Moog 和钢琴，而 Lady Gaga 提供了和声。 。</p><p>在出现在<a href="/artists/zane-lowe">Zane Lowe</a>的 Apple Music 1 节目中讨论这首歌时，Mick Jagger 分享道：“这一切都是现场演奏的。当然，我们也进行了配音，但都是在房间里播放的。是的，有那么一刻，尤其是在我们有史蒂夫的那次会议上，你感觉到了一点出路，然后你做了灵魂的结局，这就是你有时在舞台上所做的，你停下来然后开始。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="天籁之音" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JYhIXwWn9TQ?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>这位滚石主唱还谈到了与 Gaga 的合作。 “她是一位非常出色的歌手，我以前从未听过她唱过那种风格的歌。不完全是。我们在房间里现场表演，那是一次很棒的经历，她刚走进房间，就敞开心扉，看到自己的部分，感受自己的方式，然后变得更加自信。”</p><p> 《Sweet Sounds Of Heaven》是滚石乐队即将发行的唱片《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">Hackney Diamonds</a> 》中发行的第二首歌曲。继主打单曲“ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">Angry</a> ”之后，该单曲还附带了由<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/euphoria"><em>Euphoria</em></a>明星 Sydney Sweeney 主演的音乐录影带。</p><p><a href="/artists/paul-mccartney">保罗·麦卡特尼</a>和<a href="/artist/elton-john">埃尔顿·约翰</a>也参与了这张专辑，其中麦卡在“Bite My Head Off”中演奏贝斯，约翰在“Get Close”和“Live By The Sword”中演奏钢琴。</p><p> 《Hackney Diamonds》标志着乐队18年来首张原创唱片，也是乐队<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-drummer-charlie-watts-dies-aged-80-3027713">自鼓手查理·沃茨去世后的</a>首张专辑。它定于 10 月 20 日通过 Polydor 发布。 </p><figure id="attachment_3506080" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3506080" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3506080" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS.jpg" alt="滚石乐队“Hackney Diamonds”专辑封面。图片来源：新闻界" width="2000" height="2000" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS-400x400.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS-800x800.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS-696x696.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS-1392x1392.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Rolling-Stones-Hackney-Diamonds-album-artwork.-Credit-PRESS-1068x1068.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3506080" class="wp-caption-text">滚石乐队“Hackney Diamonds”专辑封面。图片来源：新闻界</figcaption></figure><p>在滚石乐队的其他新闻中， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-says-using-ai-in-music-is-like-toy-town-3505948">基思·理查兹最近表示，在音乐中使用人工智能就像“玩具城”</a> 。</p><p>理查兹作为特邀嘉宾<em><a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/sounds/play/p0gfnxd9" target="_blank" rel="noopener">与安妮 [Mac] 和尼克 [Grimshaw] 一起出现在《Sidetracked》</a></em>第一集中，分享了他对人工智能、音乐真实性和黑胶唱片作用的看法。</p><p> “如果你真的想好好听一张唱片……我的意思是数字是玩具城，”他说。 “合成器，不是你有人工智能，这更肤浅……但人工智能就像其他任何东西一样。它可以是一个工具，也可以是一个玩具。大多数时候，所有这些东西都变成了玩具。但这就像你如何使用它一样。”</p><p>贾格尔还表示，滚石乐队的旧目录<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mick-jagger-suggests-rolling-stones-back-catalogue-could-be-given-charity-3505225">最终可能会捐献给慈善机构，而不是出售或留给“不需要它”的孩子们</a>。</p><p> “孩子们不需要 5 亿美元就能过上好日子。来吧，”他说。 “你也许会为世界做一些好事，”他在透露了音乐的潜在计划后补充道。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-share-lady-gaga-and-stevie-wonder-featuring-new-single-sweet-sounds-of-heaven-3506066">滚石乐队分享 Lady Gaga 和 Stevie Wonder 的新单曲“Sweet Sounds Of Heaven”的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
